  "name": "Hyperthyroidism - Methimazole Prescription Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find hyperthyroid patients via methimazole. Methimazole is highly hyperthyroid-specific (no other indications).",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed methimazole.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on methimazole.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed methimazole — an antithyroid drug used to treat hyperthyroidism / Graves' disease.",
    "expert": "I need to find patients who have been prescribed methimazole, the primary antithyroid medication used to treat hyperthyroidism. Search MedicationRequest resources for methimazole coded in RxNorm. Methimazole is highly specific to hyperthyroidism management — unlike many other medications, it has no meaningful cross-indications, so a medication-only cohort is a reliable proxy for the hyperthyroid population."
  },
